1. Unit Testing (Backend)
Tools: JUnit, Mockito (for Java-based backend)

Test Cases:
‚úÖ Verify that a new story can be created with valid inputs.
‚úÖ Validate error handling when required fields (title, content) are missing.
‚úÖ Check if stories are correctly fetched based on ID or user.
‚úÖ Test the update functionality (modifying a story).
‚úÖ Test the delete functionality (soft delete if applicable).
‚úÖ Ensure database constraints are followed (e.g., unique story ID).

2. API Testing (Integration)
Tools: Postman, RestAssured

Test Cases:
‚úÖ POST /stories ‚Üí Create a new story with valid data.
‚úÖ POST /stories ‚Üí Send an empty request and verify error handling.
‚úÖ GET /stories/{id} ‚Üí Fetch a specific story and validate response.
‚úÖ GET /stories ‚Üí Fetch all stories and check pagination.
‚úÖ PUT /stories/{id} ‚Üí Update a story and check if the changes are reflected.
‚úÖ DELETE /stories/{id} ‚Üí Delete a story and confirm it no longer appears in the list.
‚úÖ Authorization Checks: Ensure only authorized users can create, edit, or delete a story.

3. UI Testing (Frontend)
Tools: Selenium, Cypress, Playwright

Test Cases:
‚úÖ Verify that the UI correctly displays a list of stories.
‚úÖ Ensure users can create a new story via the UI form.
‚úÖ Check if error messages appear when invalid data is submitted.
‚úÖ Test if clicking on a story opens the detailed view.
‚úÖ Ensure users can edit and save a story successfully.
‚úÖ Verify that the delete button removes a story from the UI and backend.
